Questions:
What is the primary objective of the clinical study led by Director Zeng Xi at the First Affiliated Hospital of Zhengzhou University?
A) To assess the impact of physical exercise on cognitive function post-stroke;
B) To investigate the clinical effects of intermittent nasogastric tube feeding on swallowing disorders in stroke patients;
C) To evaluate the effectiveness of aspirin in preventing secondary strokes;
D) To determine the benefits of a new blood pressure medication for stroke survivors.

Correct answer: B

Which of the following procedures is considered experimental in the context of this study for treating post-stroke pharyngeal dysphagia?
A) Routine rehabilitation including intervention for risk factors and pharmacological treatment;
B) Swallowing function training exercises for the vocal folds, pharyngeal, and laryngeal muscles;
C) Stellate Ganglion Block (SGB) with Lidocaine and Vitamin B12 injections;
D) Isotonic/isometric swallowing exercises and the Mendelsohn maneuver.

Correct answer: C

Who is responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your personal information if you participate in the study?
A) The research team and sponsors;
B) The public media;
C) All hospital staff members;
D) Only the principal investigator.

Correct answer: A) The research team and sponsors;
